      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"grand design\" thing is what really worries me though. If they're doing this on purpose, it feels like it's not just about \"mood\"—it feels way more systematic. Like, is this something big corporations use to make sure customers aren't too rebellious or critical while they're shopping? How would they even implement something like that across the whole industry?",
